# React + TypeScript Rules

## Component Standards
- Use functional components only
- Define props interfaces for all components
- Use React.memo for performance-critical components
- Extract complex logic into custom hooks
- Follow hooks rules (no conditional hooks)

## TypeScript Standards
- Use strict TypeScript with explicit types
- Prefer interfaces over type aliases for object shapes
- Use string enums for constants
- Always handle async/await with proper error handling

## Extension Popup Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS classes primarily
- Use the established color palette (apple-red, apple-pink, etc.)
- Ensure responsive design for popup constraints (width ~360px)
- Use glass-effect and gradient classes from existing styles

## Website Styling
- Use CSS classes from globals.css (`.card`, `.btn-primary`, `.gradient-text`)
- Use inline `style={{}}` for colors (Tailwind v4 var() compatibility)
- Standard Tailwind for layout only

## Component Pattern
```typescript
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  onAction: () => void;
  isLoading?: boolean;
}

export const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = React.memo(
  ({ title, onAction, isLoading = false }) => {
    return (
      <div className="p-4">
        <h2>{title}</h2>
        <button onClick={onAction} disabled={isLoading}>
          {isLoading ? "Loading..." : "Action"}
        </button>
      </div>
    );
  },
);

Component.displayName = "Component";
```
